<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">EQ Hacker gets Hacked</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=554260" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
Alright, so I have gotten a lot of emails requesting that I post this link to a thread, which announces the personal details of a "hacker" of 4 to 5 EverQuest accounts.
<p>
Now, what exactly constitutes being called a hacker? I would say it is forceful entry into an individual's account without his knowledge or consent. But apparently "hacking" to this troop is giving the individual their passwords and trusting this "hacker" with their accounts, only to have him backstab them in the end. 
<p>
Although he had deleted epics, items, sold droppable loot on Ebay/PlayerAuctions, and fully deleted some characters, one fact does remain... passwords were GIVEN out. So, take this as a lesson, and do <b>NOT</b> give out your account information. I don't care if that sexy dark elven female with the bubble butt and extremely large chest is sitting right next to you in <b>his</b> Snoopy boxers, sipping a V8 Splash... <b>DO NOT GIVE OUT YOUR ACCOUNT INFORMATION</b>!!!
<p>
<b><i><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/ftunaregeneral.showMessage?topicID=12210.topic" target="_blank">And that concludes today's lesson in not being stupid. Here's the link to that "famous" thread on the haxx0r</a></b></i>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
