	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   To the poster below, before you start spouting off about the so called &quot;poor victim&quot; of the posting of his personal info, go to school and learn some facts. Granted the people were morons for willingly handing out their account info, but this 15 year old boy, broke quite a few laws. <BR>
   Let's begin with him duping these people out of their account info. There was no actual law that he broke except the one of trust with these account holders, like I stated above that was their fault. But he did break numerous laws that he can be prosecuted for and at his age he, depending on the area he lives in he can be tried as an adult. <BR>
   His selling of the account merchandise over the internet can be likened to the charge of Receiving stolen property, since he sold items that truly did not belong to him and were obtained through deception. RSP is a felony in most states and depending on how many victims there were there can be that many counts in an indictment. <BR>
    His receiving a total of $13000 in RL currency after selling these items is known as Grand Larceny, a felony charge as well, and who knows how many people again to stack up the count.<BR>
    And last but not least this young man commited Interstate Wire Fraud, a Federal offense, by selling stolen merchandise over the internet for RL monetary gain. <BR>
     More than likely you didnt think of these facts before you shot your mouth of. If anyone should be alerting the authorities, it would be the victims of this little jerk.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
